       nnbbeesstt--mmiixx reads a number of N-best lists (which must  con-
       tain identical hypotheses), computes the hypothesis poste-
       rior probabilities for each, and computes a new  posterior
       distribution  that is a weighted mixture of the input dis-
       tributions.  The hypothesis with the highest combined pos-
       terior probability is printed.

       The  command  line  arguments  form an alternating list of
       weight values and N-best file names.

